eld following engine failure.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42504|id= 19611102-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1962|06|04}}\n|align=center|CCCP-42491 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|BUL|1946}}[[Sofia]] \n|align=center|{{nts|5}}/5\n|Struck a mountain following engine failure.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42491|id= 19620604-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1962|06|30}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42370\n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Krasnoyarsk Krai]]\n|align=center|{{nts|84}}/84\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 902]]''' crashed after it was accidentally shot down by a missile.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42370|id= 19620630-2|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1962|09|03}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42366 \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}} [[Khabarovsk]]\n|align=center|{{nts|86}}/86\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 03|Aeroflot Flight 3]]''' lost control at {{convert|4500|m|ft|abbr=on}} while climbing. Although the cause was not determined, issues with the autopilot were blamed. An accidental shoot-down by a missile was also theorized.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42366|id= 19620903-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=335|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0410 \u0414\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0413\u0412\u0424 \u0431\u043b\u0438\u0437 \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 near Khabarovsk|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1962|10|25}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42495 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Sheremetyevo International Airport|Sheremetyevo]]\n|align=center|{{nts|11}}/11\n|Crashed on takeoff during a test flight due to cross-connected rudder controls.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42495|id= 19621025-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1963|03|16}} \n|align=center|OK-LDB \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|India}}[[Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport|Santa Cruz Airport]] \n|{{unknown}}\n|Caught fire while being refueled.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= OK-LDB|id= 19630316-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1963|05|18}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42483 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Leningrad]] \n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Stalled on approach and crashed.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42483|id= 19630518-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1963|07|13}}\n|align=center|CCCP-42492 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}near [[Irkutsk Airport]] \n|align=center|{{nts|33}}/35\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 12]]''' crashed short of the runway due to incorrect instrument readings. Water entered the instrument wiring, causing a short circuit.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42492|id= 19630713-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=250|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0411 \u0412\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e-\u0421\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0413\u0412\u0424 \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0435 \u0418\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0430|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 near Irkutsk|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1964|06|09}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42476 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Novosibirsk]] \n|{{unknown}}\n|Overshot runway in heavy rain during second landing attempt.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42476|id= 19640609-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1969|04|28}}\n|align=center|CCCP-42436 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Irkutsk]]\n|{{unknown}}\n|Landed {{convert|600|m|ft|abbr=on}} short of runway; written off.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42436|id= 19690428-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1970|06|01}} \n|align=center|OK-NDD \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|Libya|1969}}[[Tripoli]] \n|align=center|{{nts|13}}/13\n|Crashed short of the runway after the pilot attempted an approach to runway 36.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= OK-NDD|id= 19700601-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1971|07|25}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42405 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}Irkutsk \n|align=center|{{nts|97}}/126  \n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 1912]]''' landed {{convert|150|m|abbr=on|-1}} short of the runway; breaking off the left wing. The aircraft rolled to the left and caught fire.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42405|id= 19710725-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=124|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0411 \u0422\u043e\u043b\u043c\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0410\u041e \u0432 \u0430/\u043f \u0418\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0442\u0441|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 Irkutsk Airport|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1971|10|10}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42490 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Vnukovo International Airport|Vnukovo]] \n|align=center|{{nts|25}}/25\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 773]]''' crashed shortly after takeoff after an explosion occurred while climbing through {{convert|1200|m|ft|abbr=on}}. The explosion damaged the fuselage and destroyed flight controls. Control was lost and the aircraft rolled right and entered a descent until it struck the ground. The explosion was caused by a bomb placed between the cabin wall and a passenger seat in the rear of the cabin near frame 45.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|type=Criminal|title= CCCP-42490|id= 19711010-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=124|title=\u0412\u0437\u0440\u044b\u0432 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0443 \u0422\u0443-104\u0411 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u0413\u0410 \u0431\u043b\u0438\u0437 \u0430\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043d\u0443\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e|language= Russian|trans-title= Explosion on Tu-104 near Vnukovo|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1972|03|19}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42408 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Omsk]] \n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Struck a snow wall short of the runway during the fifth landing attempt.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42408|id= 19720319-2|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|04|24}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42505 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Leningrad]] \n|align=center|{{nts|2}}/57\n|Hijacked by a passenger who demanded to be taken to Sweden. The crew returned to Leningrad. While the landing gear was lowered, the hijacker set off a bomb, killing himself and the flight engineer. The bomb blew a hole in the fuselage, but the aircraft was able to land safely.\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u2116: CCCP-42505|url=http://russianplanes.net/reginfo/9708|accessdate=11 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42505|id= 19730424-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|05|18}} \n|align=center|\u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420-42379 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Buryat Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic|Buryat ASSR]] \n|align=center|{{nts|82}}/82\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 109]]''' was hijacked by a passenger who demanded to be taken to China. A bomb that the hijacker had put on board the aircraft detonated at {{convert|30000|ft|m|abbr=on}} and the aircraft lost control and crashed east of Lake Baikal.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|type=Hijacking|title= CCCP-42411|id= 19730518-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=102|title=\u0412\u0437\u0440\u044b\u0432 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0443 \u0438 \u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0410 \u0412\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e-\u0421\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u0413\u0410 \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0435 \u0427\u0438\u0442\u044b|language= Russian|trans-title= Explosion on Tu-104 Chita region|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|08|29}} \n|align=center|OK-MDE \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|Cyprus|1960}}[[Nicosia]] \n|align=center|{{nts|0}}/70\n|'''CSA Flight 531''' veered off the runway after landing after the pilot failed to stop the aircraft in time. The wreckage remains at the airport site to this day.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= OK-MDE|id= 19730829-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|09|30}}\n|align=center|CCCP-42506 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Yekaterinburg|Sverdlovsk]] \n|align=center|{{nts|108}}/108\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 3932]]''' crashed shortly after takeoff due to a power failure of the artificial horizons. \n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42506|id= 19730930-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|10|13}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42486 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Domodedovo (town)|Domodedovo]] \n|align=center|{{nts|122}}/122\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 964]]''' crashed while on approach following a power failure to the compass system and main gyros and resulting loss of control. The crash is the worst involving the Tu-104.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42486|id= 19731013-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1973|12|7}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42503 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}near [[Moscow]] \n|align=center|{{nts|16}}/75\n|'''Aeroflot Flight 964''' crashed after a wing struck the ground after coming in too fast.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42503|id= 19731207-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=63|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0411 \u0413\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u0413\u0410 \u0432 \u0430/\u043f \u0414\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u043e|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 Domodedovo Airport|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1974|11|05}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42501 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}Chita \n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Overran the runway on landing and came to rest against a railway embankment.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42501|id= 19741105-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1975|08|30}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42472 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Tolmachevo Airport]] \n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Right landing gear collapsed following a heavy landing.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42472|id= 19750830-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1976|02|09}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42327 \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}Irkutsk \n|align=center|{{nts|24}}/115\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 3739 (1976)|Aeroflot Flight 3739]]''' crashed after banking to the right while climbing for takeoff and entering a descent. Debris from the aircraft struck a North Korean Tu-154 that had just landed. Although the official cause of the accident was loss of control caused by crosswinds, improper fueling (too much fuel on one side) and pilot error were also theorized.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42327|id= 19760209-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=118|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0410 \u0412\u0421 \u0423\u0413\u0410 \u0432 \u0418\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0435|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 Irkutsk|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1976|07|17}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42335\n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Chita Airport]]\n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Failed to take off and crashed due to overloading.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42335|id= 19760717-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1976|11|28}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42471 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}near [[Sheremetyevo]] \n|align=center|{{nts|72}}/72\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 2415]]''' lost control and crashed following artificial horizon failure and resulting crew disorientation.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42471|id= 19761128-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=52|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0411 \u041b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0410\u041e \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0435 \u0430/\u043f \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0435\u0432\u043e|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 Sheremetyevo/Leningrad area|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1976}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42371 \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Borispol Airport]] \n|{{unknown}}\n|Crashed short of the runway after the engines were shut down in flight.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42438|id= 19769999-4|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1977|1|13}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42369 \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Almaty|Alma-Ata]] \n|align=center|{{nts|96}}/96\n|'''[[Aeroflot Flight 3843]]''' exploded in mid-air due to an engine fire.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42369|id= 19770113-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.airdisaster.ru/database.php?id=56|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0430 \u0422\u0443-104\u0410 \u0414\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u0413\u0410 \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0435 \u0430/\u043f \u0410\u043b\u043c\u0430-\u0410\u0442\u0430|language= Russian|trans-title= Accident Tu-104 near Alma-Ata Airport|publisher= airdisaster.ru|accessdate= 2015-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1979|3|17}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42444 \n|align=center|Tu-104B\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}near Moscow \n|align=center|{{nts|58}}/119\n|While operating as '''[[Aeroflot Flight 1691]]''', the crew encountered a false fire alarm from engine during takeoff and turned back to Vnukovo. The plane crashed while attempting to return to the airport. Aeroflot removed the Tu-104 from service following this accident.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42444|id= 19790317-1|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1981|2|7}} \n|align=center|CCCP-42332 \n|align=center|Tu-104A\n|{{flagicon|USSR}}[[Pushkin (town)|Pushkin]] \n|align=center|{{nts|50}}/50\n|Soviet Navy flight; [[1981 Pushkin Tu-104 crash]], failed to take off due to shifting cargo. All military Tu-104's were grounded following this accident.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= CCCP-42332|id= 19810207-0|accessdate= 2015-12-15}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Specifications (Tu-104B)==\n[[File:Tupoljev Tu-104.svg|right|350px]]\n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=Tupolev Tu-104: Aeroflot's first jet<ref name=gordonrigmant>{{cite book |last=Gordon |first=Yefim |title=Tupolev Tu-104: Aeroflot's first jet |year=2007 |publisher=Midland |location=Hinkley |isbn=978-1-85780-265-8 |last2=Rigmant |first2= Vladimir |page=36}}</ref>, Tupolew / Tupolev Tu-104<ref name=flugzeuginfo>{{cite web|url=http://www.flugzeuginfo.net/acdata_php/acdata_tu104_en.php|title=Tupolew / Tupolev Tu-104|author=|date=|website=www.flugzeuginfo.net|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n|prime units?=met\n<!--\n        General characteristics\n-->\n|crew=7\n|capacity=50\u2013115 passengers\n|length m=40.06\n|length note=\n|span m=34.54\n|span note=\n|height m=11.9\n|height note=\n|wing area sqm=183\n|wing area note=less [[LERX]]\n|aspect ratio=<!-- sailplanes -->\n|airfoil='''root:''' PR-1-10S-9 (15.7%) ; '''tip:''' PR-1-10S-9 (12%)<ref name=\"Selig\">{{cite web |last1=Lednicer |first1=David |title=The Incomplete Guide to Airfoil Usage |url=https://m-selig.ae.illinois.edu/ads/aircraft.html |website=m-selig.ae.illinois.edu |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n|empty weight kg=43800\n|empty weight note=\n|gross weight kg=78100\n|gross weight note=\n|max takeoff weight kg=\n|max takeoff weight note=\n|fuel capacity={{cvt|21000|kg|0}} normal ; {{cvt|26500|kg|0}} maximum\n|more general=\n<!--\n        Powerplant\n-->\n|eng1 number=2\n|eng1 name=[[Mikulin AM-3M-500]]\n|eng1 type=[[turbojet]] engines\n|eng1 kw=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 hp=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 shp=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 kn=<!-- jet/rocket engines -->\n|eng1 lbf=21400\n|eng1 note=\n<!--\n        Performance\n-->\n|max speed kmh=950\n|max speed note=<br/>\n*'''Cruising speed:''' {{cvt|750|-|8